Yeh aik bohot common aur important requirement hai, kyunki jab aapke project mein 100 models ho jayenge, toh aap har baar saare models nahi chalana chahenge.

dbt mein kisi aik specific file ya model ko chalane ke liye hum **`--select`** flag (ya sirf **`-s`**) use karte hain.

---

### 1. Single Model Chalane ki Command

Agar aapki file ka naam `stg_customers.sql` hai, toh aap ye command chalayenge:

```bash
docker exec -it dbt_container dbt run --select stg_customers
```

_(Note: `.sql` extension likhne ki zaroorat nahi hoti, sirf file ka naam kaafi hai)._

---

### 2. Useful Variations (Pro Tips)

Dbt mein select karne ke kuch aur zabardast tareeqe bhi hain:

- **Model aur uske aglay (Downstream) models:**
  Agar aap chahte hain ke `stg_customers` chale aur us par depend karne wale saare aglay models bhi chal jayen:
  `dbt run --select stg_customers+` (Aakhir mein **+** lagayein).

- **Model aur uske pichly (Upstream) models:**
  Agar aap chahte hain ke model chale aur wo jin sources se data le raha hai wo bhi process hon:
  `dbt run --select +stg_customers` (Shuru mein **+** lagayein).

- **Pura Folder Chalana:**
  Agar aapne models ko folders mein rakha hai (maslan `models/marts/`), toh aap pura folder bhi chala sakte hain:
  `dbt run --select marts`

---

### 3. Sirf Test Chalana

Agar aapne us specific model ke liye tests likhe hain aur sirf unhein check karna chahte hain:
`docker exec -it dbt_container dbt test --select stg_customers`

